              ]
            }
          ],
          "SAMPLE": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": null,
              "free_text": [
                "Two liquid hydrogen targets were used which had total",
                "surface  densities of 1.31 and 1.11 g/cm2. The",
                "evaporation rate from the target was about 10 cm3 of",
                "liquid hydrogen per hour when most of the ortho-",
                "parahydrogen conversion had taken place."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "DETECTOR": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "TELES"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                " A triple coincidence range telescope was used",
                "to detect the scattered protons and the telescope",
                "absorber was changed in order to maintain constant",
                "efficiency of detection for the different scattering",
                "angles. The counter telescope was mounted on an arm",
                "which could be swung from side to side of the beam",
                "direction and whose pivot was carefully set in the",
                "centre of the collimated beam."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "CORRECTION": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": null,
              "free_text": [
                "To obtain the true efficiency for any scattering",
                "angle a small correction was added to the measured",
                "value for those protons which were lost before being",
                "detected by the telescope. This correction was",
                "slightly energy sensitive amounting to 0.2% at 10 degr.",
                "and 0.6% at 40 degrees for the 98 MeV determination."
              ]
            }
          ],
